[Mark 15:7](../../../bib/kjv/mar015.htm#007.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_007">mar 15:7</span></span>

Insurrection - A crime which the Roman governors, and Pilate in
particular, were more especially concerned and careful to punish.

[Mark 15:9](../../../bib/kjv/mar015.htm#009.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_009">mar 15:9</span></span>

Will ye that I release to you the king of the Jews - Which does this
wretched man discover most? Want of justice, or courage, or common
sense? The poor coward sacrifices justice to popular clamour, and
enrages those whom he seeks to appease, by so unseasonably repeating
that title, The king of the Jews, which he could not but know was so
highly offensive to them.

[Mark 15:16](../../../bib/kjv/mar015.htm#016.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_016">mar 15:16</span></span>

Praetorium - The inner hall, where the praetor, a Roman magistrate, used
to give judgment. But St. John calls the whole palace by this name. [Mat
27:27](../../../bib/kjv/mat027.htm#027.md); [Joh
19:2](../../../bib/kjv/joh019.htm#002.md).

[Mark 15:17](../../../bib/kjv/mar015.htm#017.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_017">mar 15:17</span></span>

Purple - As royal robes were usually purple and scarlet, St. Mark and
John term this a purple robe, St. Matthew a scarlet one. The Tyrian
purple is said not to have been very different from scarlet.

[Mark 15:20](../../../bib/kjv/mar015.htm#020.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_020">mar 15:20</span></span>

[Mat 27:31](../../../bib/kjv/mat027.htm#031.md); [Joh
19:16](../../../bib/kjv/joh019.htm#016.md).

[Mark 15:21](../../../bib/kjv/mar015.htm#021.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_021">mar 15:21</span></span>

The father of Alexander and Rufus - These were afterward two eminent
Christians, and must have been well known when St. Mark wrote.

