[Mark 15:41](../../../bib/kjv/mar015.htm#041.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_041">mar 15:41</span></span>

Who served him - Provided him with necessaries.

[Mark 15:42](../../../bib/kjv/mar015.htm#042.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_042">mar 15:42</span></span>

Because it was the day before the Sabbath - And the bodies might not
hang on the Sabbath day: therefore they were in haste to have them taken
down.

[Mark 15:43](../../../bib/kjv/mar015.htm#043.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_043">mar 15:43</span></span>

Honourable - A man of character and reputation: A counsellor - A member
of the sanhedrim. Who waited for the kingdom of God - Who expected to
see it set up on earth. [Mat 27:57](../../../bib/kjv/mat027.htm#057.md);
[Luk 23:50](../../../bib/kjv/luk023.htm#050.md); [Joh
19:38](../../../bib/kjv/joh019.htm#038.md).

[Mark 15:46](../../../bib/kjv/mar015.htm#046.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_046">mar 15:46</span></span>

He rolled a stone - By his servants. It was too large for him to roll
himself.

